issue.title: Fix load failure for onnx model with external data and slash (/) in path [Windows]

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

GetDirNameFromFilePath currently assumes path using backslash. If user gives a ONNX model with external data, and path uses slash (/) instead of backslash (\\), ORT cannot extract the directory from path to locate external data file.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

Related issues: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/5418, #11708

body:
Thanks a lot @yuslepukhin and @tianleiwu , the use of  "\\\\" is the solution.

`ort_session = ort.InferenceSession('C:\\Users\\Jorge\\PycharmProjects\\inteBERT\\onnx\\model.onnx', options)`
